DIT-5: Home portability + teardown
Operator-attested: 2026-07-15
Verdict: PASS

Scope and provenance
--------------------

This is a redacted transcript of a live disposable-Home run. Paths below are
labels for disposable locations; no archive or portability envelope is committed.

The historical GitHub v0.66.0 release asset was no longer available. The source
side therefore used a real packaged release built from the exact annotated
v0.66.0 tag at commit 08d821bb. The target side used the locally packaged 1.0.1
release candidate. The binary-uninstall leg independently used the published,
cosign-verified v1.0.0 macOS arm64 artifact installed into a disposable prefix.

  $ $V066_PACKAGE/bin/allbert --version
  allbert 0.66.0

  $ $V101_PACKAGE/bin/allbert --version
  allbert 1.0.1

Source Home preparation
-----------------------

The v0.66.0 package was pointed at $SOURCE_HOME. A connected notes root at
$CONNECTED_NOTES contained marker DIT5-CONNECTED-NOTE-20260715. One memory with
marker DIT5-KEPT-MEMORY-20260715 was reviewed to status :kept.

  $ ALLBERT_HOME=$SOURCE_HOME $V066_PACKAGE/bin/allbert admin notes show
  Notes root: $CONNECTED_NOTES

  $ ALLBERT_HOME=$SOURCE_HOME $V066_PACKAGE/bin/allbert admin memory list --status kept
  dit5-kept-marker status=kept

  $ ALLBERT_HOME=$SOURCE_HOME $V066_PACKAGE/bin/allbert admin memory retrieve --query DIT5-KEPT-MEMORY-20260715
  Retrieved 1 active chunk.
  Status: completed

Portability envelope and file-level transfer
--------------------------------------------

The v0.66 packaged CLI had a historical defect: `admin home export --out` ignored
the output path. The same exact-tag implementation was therefore invoked through
its Mix task to produce the authentic redacted envelope. The Home payload itself
moved separately at file level, as required by the corrected DIT-5 runbook.

  $ ALLBERT_HOME=$SOURCE_HOME MIX_ENV=prod mix allbert.home.export --out $ENVELOPE
  Exported redacted Allbert Home envelope.
  envelope_version=1 fragments=49 files=11 secret_refs=0 redacted=true

  $ shasum -a 256 $ENVELOPE $HOME_ARCHIVE
  c323815003f7256c1ea976faa407b46d7ed018df5f45cbbb1682bf92886019bd  $ENVELOPE
  8e634ccf2cc1e767ea178d48695e7fd55b745f88303f9499ac52f63949d85878  $HOME_ARCHIVE

  $ tar -C $TRANSFER_ROOT -xzf $HOME_ARCHIVE
  [exit 0]

Upgrade validation against transferred Home
-------------------------------------------

The 1.0.1 package opened $TRANSFER_HOME, ran its migrations during normal startup,
and validated the envelope as a dry run only. The representative kept-memory file
was byte-identical before and after import validation.

  $ shasum -a 256 $TRANSFER_HOME/memory/identity/dit5-kept-marker.md
  2547857147ab536f4e18f23e6953777c409a2df8a679b2f3282e8b626a97b42d  .../dit5-kept-marker.md

  $ ALLBERT_HOME=$TRANSFER_HOME $V101_PACKAGE/bin/allbert admin home import $ENVELOPE
  import dry-run

  $ shasum -a 256 $TRANSFER_HOME/memory/identity/dit5-kept-marker.md
  2547857147ab536f4e18f23e6953777c409a2df8a679b2f3282e8b626a97b42d  .../dit5-kept-marker.md

  $ ALLBERT_HOME=$TRANSFER_HOME $V101_PACKAGE/bin/allbert admin health
  Health: ok.
  service_platform=launchd service_manager_available=true

  $ ALLBERT_HOME=$TRANSFER_HOME $V101_PACKAGE/bin/allbert admin notes show
  Notes root: $CONNECTED_NOTES

  $ ALLBERT_HOME=$TRANSFER_HOME $V101_PACKAGE/bin/allbert admin memory list --status kept
  dit5-kept-marker status=kept

  $ ALLBERT_HOME=$TRANSFER_HOME $V101_PACKAGE/bin/allbert admin memory retrieve --query DIT5-KEPT-MEMORY-20260715
  Retrieved 1 active chunk.
  Status: completed

Confirmation-gated service uninstall
------------------------------------

A disposable launchd user agent was registered under the disposable target user
root. The real user service and plist were confirmed absent before setup. The
product uninstall first created a durable confirmation and changed nothing; the
operator then approved that exact request. The target resumed and completed.

  $ ALLBERT_HOME=$TRANSFER_HOME $V101_PACKAGE/bin/allbert admin service uninstall
  Service uninstall is ready for approval. Confirmation request: conf_1784150511000000_771. Nothing was changed.

  $ ALLBERT_HOME=$TRANSFER_HOME $V101_PACKAGE/bin/allbert admin confirmations approve conf_1784150511000000_771 --reason "DIT-5 disposable service uninstall proof"
  conf_1784150511000000_771 status=approved
  Resolver: local/cli
  Target: service_control status=completed

  $ launchctl print gui/$UID/com.lexlapax.allbert
  Could not find service "com.lexlapax.allbert" in domain for user gui: $UID

  $ test -e $DISPOSABLE_USER/Library/LaunchAgents/com.lexlapax.allbert.plist
  [exit 1: removed]

Published binary uninstall without purge
----------------------------------------

The published v1.0.0 macOS arm64 artifact was downloaded into $DISPOSABLE_PREFIX
through scripts/install/install.sh. Its checksum and cosign bundle verified before
installation. The uninstall command was run without --purge.

  $ ALLBERT_VERSION=1.0.0 ALLBERT_PREFIX=$DISPOSABLE_PREFIX ALLBERT_HOME=$TRANSFER_HOME sh scripts/install/install.sh
  allbert: verifying release signature
  Verified OK
  allbert: verifying checksum
  allbert: installing to $DISPOSABLE_PREFIX/lib/allbert
  allbert: installed.

  $ ALLBERT_HOME=$TRANSFER_HOME $DISPOSABLE_PREFIX/bin/allbert --version
  allbert 1.0.0

  $ ALLBERT_PREFIX=$DISPOSABLE_PREFIX ALLBERT_HOME=$TRANSFER_HOME sh scripts/install/uninstall.sh
  allbert: removed installed files.
  allbert: Allbert Home preserved. Re-run with --purge to remove your data.

  $ test -e $DISPOSABLE_PREFIX/bin/allbert
  [exit 1: removed]

Home preservation after both uninstall legs
-------------------------------------------

  $ test -d $TRANSFER_HOME
  [exit 0]

  $ shasum -a 256 $TRANSFER_HOME/memory/identity/dit5-kept-marker.md $CONNECTED_NOTES/dit5-connected-note.md
  2547857147ab536f4e18f23e6953777c409a2df8a679b2f3282e8b626a97b42d  .../dit5-kept-marker.md
  80c96d354c472a25792a352f11c8f91d12bd41ad1cf66dd98ef71a590261f0cb  .../dit5-connected-note.md

PASS: the exact-tag v0.66.0 packaged Home transferred to the 1.0.1 package;
the redacted envelope validated without applying; health, connected notes, and
the :kept memory survived; confirmation-gated service uninstall completed; the
published binary uninstall removed installed files without --purge; Allbert Home
and both representative marker hashes remained intact.
